history.content:
When I took it last semester with Babak, there wasn't discussion on the first week.

Quoted from his recent email, if anyone is wondering.

 

 

Hi folks,

Welcome to, or back to, Berkeley, and to EE 20.

This is just a quick note to tell you that I'll be starting lectures in the afternoon section starting next Tuesday, right after Labor Day weekend.  There are no labs or discussions this week.

Our delayed start is due to several reasons, including late allocation of TAs, which has to do with budget issues being sorted out late by the campus.

In any event, with this move we join other self-respecting semester-based peer institutions (such as MIT) that begin instruction after Labor Day---the way it ought to be!

We'll make up for the lecture time in a graceful way downstream.

See you next week in lecture.  And stay out of trouble and be safe this weekend.

Cheers,

Babak.
